  <!-- ═══ Section 8: Deep Dive ═══ -->
  <section id="deep-dive" class="section">
    <p class="section-label"
      data-i18n-en="Deep Dive"
      data-i18n-zh="深入探讨">Deep Dive</p>
    <h2 data-i18n-en="The Mathematics"
        data-i18n-zh="数学推导">The Mathematics</h2>

    <details>
      <summary data-i18n-en="SDE Formulation"
               data-i18n-zh="随机微分方程形式">SDE Formulation</summary>
      <div class="math-block">
        <Math tex={String.raw`dX_t^i = \left(-\nabla V(X_t^i) - \frac{1}{N}\sum_{j \neq i} \nabla\Phi(X_t^i - X_t^j)\right) dt + \sigma\, dW_t^i`} />
      </div>
      <p data-i18n-en="Each particle's motion is governed by three forces: confinement V, mean-field interaction &Phi;, and Brownian noise &sigma;."
         data-i18n-zh="每个粒子的运动受三种力支配：束缚势V、平均场交互&Phi;和布朗噪声&sigma;。">
        Each particle's motion is governed by three forces: confinement V, mean-field interaction &Phi;, and Brownian noise &sigma;.
      </p>
    </details>

    <details>
      <summary data-i18n-en="Weak Form PDE &amp; Self-Test Derivation"
               data-i18n-zh="弱形式 PDE 与自测推导">Weak Form PDE &amp; Self-Test Derivation</summary>
      <div class="math-block">
        <Math tex={String.raw`\underbrace{\delta E_{\text{tot}}}_{\text{energy change}} \;=\; \underbrace{\frac{\sigma^2}{2}\, J_{\text{diff}}\, \Delta t}_{\text{diffusion}} \;-\; \underbrace{J_{\text{diss}}\, \Delta t}_{\text{dissipation}} \;+\; \text{martingale}`} />
      </div>
      <p data-i18n-en="Applying Ito's formula to the energy functional E = &lt;V + &Phi;*&mu;, &mu;&gt; with the unknowns as test functions. The 1/2 self-test coefficient arises from using the variation perspective (testing against V,&Phi; themselves) rather than energy balance matching (which leads to 4th-order equations)."
         data-i18n-zh="以能量泛函 E = &lt;V + &Phi;*&mu;, &mu;&gt; 应用伊藤公式，用未知量本身作为测试函数。1/2 自测系数来自变分视角（用 V,&Phi; 自身做测试），而非能量平衡匹配（那会导致4阶方程）。">
        Applying Ito's formula to the energy functional with the unknowns as test functions. The 1/2 self-test coefficient arises from the variation perspective, not energy balance matching.
      </p>
    </details>

    <details>
      <summary data-i18n-en="Self-Test Loss Function"
               data-i18n-zh="自测损失函数">Self-Test Loss Function</summary>
      <div class="math-block">
        <Math tex={String.raw`\mathbb{E}\!\left[\mathcal{L}(V^*, \Phi^*)\right] = -\frac{1}{2}\,\mathbb{E}\!\left[J_{\text{diss}}^*\, \Delta t\right] < 0 \qquad \text{vs.} \qquad \mathcal{L}(0, 0) = 0`} />
      </div>
      <p data-i18n-en="The key innovation: the (1/2) coefficient on the dissipation term means L(V*, &Phi;*) = -(1/2) E[J_diss &Delta;t] < 0, while L(0,0) = 0. This breaks the trivial-solution degeneracy."
         data-i18n-zh="关键创新：耗散项上的(1/2)系数意味着 L(V*, &Phi;*) = -(1/2) E[J_diss &Delta;t] < 0，而 L(0,0) = 0。这打破了平凡解的退化性。">
        The key innovation: the (1/2) coefficient on the dissipation term means L(V*, &Phi;*) = -(1/2) E[J_diss &Delta;t] &lt; 0, while L(0,0) = 0. This breaks the trivial-solution degeneracy.
      </p>
    </details>

    <details>
      <summary data-i18n-en="Neural Network Architecture"
               data-i18n-zh="神经网络架构">Neural Network Architecture</summary>
      <p data-i18n-en="Both V and &Phi; are parameterized by 3-layer MLPs with [64, 64, 64] hidden dimensions. The activation function must be C&sup2;-smooth (e.g. Softplus or Tanh) — ReLU is not allowed because the self-test loss requires computing Laplacians via automatic differentiation, which needs second derivatives to exist. The symmetry &Phi;(x) = &Phi;(-x) is enforced architecturally. Total: ~17,000 parameters."
         data-i18n-zh="V 和 &Phi; 均由 3 层 MLP 参数化，隐藏维度 [64, 64, 64]。激活函数必须是 C&sup2; 连续的（如 Softplus 或 Tanh）——不能用 ReLU，因为自测损失需要通过自动微分计算拉普拉斯量，要求二阶导数存在。对称性 &Phi;(x) = &Phi;(-x) 通过架构强制实现。总参数：约 17,000。">
        Both V and &Phi; are parameterized by 3-layer MLPs with [64, 64, 64] hidden dimensions. The activation function must be C&sup2;-smooth (e.g. Softplus or Tanh) — ReLU is not allowed because the self-test loss requires computing Laplacians via automatic differentiation, which needs second derivatives to exist. The symmetry &Phi;(x) = &Phi;(-x) is enforced architecturally. Total: ~17,000 parameters.
      </p>
    </details>
  </section>

